headline: The Kroger Co. Foundation Awards 106 Scholarships to Children of Kroger Associates
summary: The Kroger Co. (NYSE: KR) Foundation today announced the Kroger Scholars for the 2025-2026 academic year, awarding $265,000 to 106 students. All scholars are the children of Kroger associates and receive $2,500 toward any accredited two- or four-year college, university or vocational program. Launched in 2008, the Kroger Scholars Program has awarded more than $5 million in scholarship funds.

headline: Does Kroger’s Recent 24% Rally Signal More Room to Run After Layoffs News?
summary: Thinking about what to do with your Kroger stock? You are not alone lately. Whether you have been watching from the sidelines or have a few shares tucked away, this supermarket giant is giving investors a lot to consider in 2025. Despite some short-term bumps, Kroger’s long-term price chart reads like a master class in steady growth.
